Durban - Samkelo Khumalo, 33, was handed a 23-year prison sentence by the Umlazi Regional Court for rape, kidnapping and assault with the intent to cause grievous bodily harm. Colonel Thembeka Mbhele, police spokesperson, said Khumalo was sentenced on Monday after the court heard how he raped a woman. “He was sentenced to 15 years for rape, five years for kidnapping and three years for assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm,” said Mbhele. “On Freedom Day, April 27, 2016, at night, the victim, 31, was at H section informal settlement, Umlazi when she was approached by the accused. He forced her to his house where she was assaulted and raped. A case of rape, kidnapping and assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm was opened at Umlazi police station. Two days later, the Umlazi Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences unit arrested the accused and he was linked to the rape case. He appeared in the Umlazi court until he was convicted,” said Mbhele. Major General Bheki Langa, KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner said, “This will serve as a warning to those who terrorise women and children in our province. I further commended the unit for the speedily arrest of the accused.” Daily News